<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lol, CH broke the game...I'd like to see you heal any class tanking a 900-1k+ Quading mob without CH....you'd need lke 20+ healers per raid <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Montyy.. you PLAY an Ogre.. YOU are not an Ogre.. so lets not act dumb as one please.<br>
<br>
Why do you think mobs had to have those kinds of DPS and have those kinds of HP?<br>
<br>
Mobs did not at first. The normal mob DPS*HP/LVL progression starts to break at lvl 39. This game was not designed with CH in mind.<br>
<br>
VELIOUS and after was designed with CH in mind. They did it because the obvious degenerate tactic was making everything trivial. They had to break the 32k HP limit because of CH. If healing potential was linear there would have been  no need for 32k plus mobs. Things can be quite challenging inside 32k hp .. as long as healing ability is not INFINITE.<br>
<br>
Clerics healing/mana ratios by level:<br>
<br>
 1 1.0<br>
 5 1.4<br>
14 1.7<br>
24 2.0<br>
34 2.3<br>
<br>
then 39.. and healing potential becomes a product of mana pool times warrior HP, with a slight AC factor. Healing ability goes thru the roof.<br>
<br>
It SHOULD have been something like:<br>
<br>
44 2.6<br>
54 3.0<br>
60 3.5<br>
<br>
This allows a nice controlled balancing of mob power vs player power. As it stands it is a hairs breath between trivial and impossible. It's very hard to make a truly challenging encounter.<br>
<br>
In fact if not for CH, MB would not exist.. why would it have to? The whole 'caster balancing thing' would have been moot if caster power scaled the same way cleric/warrior power did.<br>
<br>
Now they can't nerf CH. Because they've built more than 2 expansions based on it. But they have stated CH was a mistake (like anyone could have not have noticed) and it will not be repeated.<br>
<br>
And Montyy, the formula was basic, but nevertheless accurate. It was not intended to be a lecture MT tactics. I jumped to the conclusion you would not need one.<br>
<br>
