<br>
Dragons?  Stay in combat and try not to be feared...how easy is that to MT?  (answer:  not easy at all, even with 400+ MR and lvl 60)<br>
<br>
VS?  Even with 10 complete healing clerics, a warrior with 7k hp can get lifetapped down in a matter of a melee round if he 'goes off' with his procs.<br>
<br>
Trak?  Trak touch, anyone?  Where'd the MT go?<br>
<br>
I think the evidence points to the fact that VI designed those encounters to actually enforce 'thinking outside the Holy Trilogy' and coming up with other methods of succeeding in those encounters.<br>
<br>
It was really only with Velious that VI obviously forgo trying to design encounters to force folks not to use complete heal and a main tank...and therefore it stands to logic that Velious and Luclin are the arenas where they intended manaburn to be used as well.<br>
<br>
Personally, I've only been run over once for a raid (VS) by a manaburn crew (or duo, or whatever).  But one cannot say the opportunity for abuse is not there, no matter how you justify the benefits of the skill in other zones.<br>
<br>
Oh, and the comparison the Lifeburn is interesting...how many dragons have you seen LB'd down?  It's not granted practical aggro immunity like MB...nor does it leave the necro with the 800+ pts of rune shielding + full hit points.  ...oh, and it doesn't crit, either...<br>
<br>
I'd hate to see it nerfed for the wizard community, it's a very handy tool in some situations.  But I don't think these mobs were given much consideration during the design of the skill, and maybe that should be changed (for just Kunark boss mobs). <p>Good travels,<br>
